<p>
    <strong>Workshop Objective</strong>
</p>

<p>
    The Home Child Care Management course is for people without formal training in early learning and

    child care and who are interested in pursuing a career in child care. Completion of this workshop will

    help you attain the knowledge of basic child care management through the introduction and

    understanding of the following key areas:
</p>

<ul>
    <li>Roles and Responsibilities</li>

    <li>Introduction to Child Development - Infant, Toddler & Preschool Development</li>

    <li>Set up and maintain a safe, clean, well-organized child care environment</li>

    <li>Plan educational activities</li>

    <li>Health and Safety</li>

    <li>Nutrition</li>

    <li>CPR</li>
</ul>

